sql:
SELECT companies.name, sectors.sector_name
FROM companies
INNER JOIN sectors ON companies.sector_id = sectors.sector_id;

SELECT report_type, report_date
FROM company_reports
WHERE company_id = 0;

external_knowledge:
- "blossoming giants" refers to large and growing companies;
- "sprouted in the new millennium" refers to companies founded after 2000;
- "financial footprint exceeds the shadows of a hundred billion dollars" means the market capitalization is over $100 billion;
- "attracted more than a cursory glance" indicates the company has been accessed more than once;
- "over ten visits from the curious multitude" refers to having more than 10 access logs.

